888
01:40:53,156 --> 01:40:57,318
I don't know anybody from my side of this issue

889
01:40:57,776 --> 01:41:00,599
who doesn't want to see Medford become a sanctuary city.

890
01:41:01,039 --> 01:41:04,543
I didn't hear a single one of them say they oppose immigration.

891
01:41:04,783 --> 01:41:19,357
In fact, I started out when I first spoke saying I encourage immigration, especially from other countries where there's oppression or just subpar standing living standards.

892
01:41:22,819 --> 01:41:28,463
It's difficult to embrace this issue on so many levels.

893
01:41:28,844 --> 01:41:45,997
But I really think it's, I mean, people want to come up here and say that, you know, just saying that the reasons why we're for honoring the law is somehow related to the Nazis or white privilege.

894
01:41:46,377 --> 01:41:50,640
And then they want to say that the statistics we bring up are fear-mongering.

895
01:41:53,289 --> 01:41:55,814
It's just a little hypocritical, Mr. President.

896
01:41:56,115 --> 01:41:58,099
I also want to address the point of

897
01:41:58,937 --> 01:42:08,225
being for limited government, but also being for a police force in Medford that's not a full force.

898
01:42:09,246 --> 01:42:12,108
It has nothing to do with limited government.

899
01:42:12,328 --> 01:42:17,492
It has everything to do with government's first duty, in my opinion, which is protection of the citizens.

900
01:42:17,933 --> 01:42:23,197
We are about 30 officers insufficient on our police force.

901
01:42:25,038 --> 01:42:26,840
In the current policy of not

902
01:42:27,521 --> 01:42:29,063
ask an immigration status.

903
01:42:29,163 --> 01:42:34,289
If that's what the police department now deems fit, then that's what I support.

904
01:42:34,770 --> 01:42:38,975
But make no mistake, what the policy for the Safe Medford

905
01:42:41,360 --> 01:42:54,526
group is, is to actually put into law, taking away any possibility of police asking, should the question arise about immigration status.

906
01:42:54,946 --> 01:42:59,828
You know, it was actually President Obama who put forward the secured community program

907
01:43:00,708 --> 01:43:14,478
which Massachusetts never actually signed on to, which automatically, if there was any question of immigration status, that fingerprints and mugshots had to be sent to ICE.

908
01:43:15,298 --> 01:43:16,299
Massachusetts never

909
01:43:17,591 --> 01:43:20,032
joined on to the Secured Communities Program.

910
01:43:20,692 --> 01:43:22,593
And I really don't know why.

911
01:43:22,653 --> 01:43:33,558
And whether it's not constitutional law or state law, I mean, there's no skirting around with legal jargon the fact that there are laws.

912
01:43:34,518 --> 01:43:37,920
that govern legal citizenship in the United States.

913
01:43:38,460 --> 01:43:42,742
And my side of the argument is that we just honor these laws.

914
01:43:43,102 --> 01:43:47,004
It has nothing to do with white supremacy or Nazism.

915
01:43:47,344 --> 01:43:55,027
It's just a simple matter of respecting the law because we are, as the founding fathers said repeatedly, a nation of laws.

916
01:43:55,227 --> 01:43:56,808
And those laws have to be respected.

917
01:43:57,288 --> 01:44:01,570
Are you circumventing the very reason why it's a good country

918
01:44:01,963 --> 01:44:02,443
to come to.

919
01:44:03,104 --> 01:44:22,913
And finally, one of the things that gets established when you establish a state or a city as a sanctuary city, you're creating a magnet for illegal residents to come to, which makes it pretty easy for ICE and for whoever is in power of immigration to know where to go to.

920
01:44:24,374 --> 01:44:32,480
So it's actually not a service to undocumented, illegal residents of the United States.

921
01:44:32,880 --> 01:44:34,822
You're actually putting a target on their back.

922
01:44:35,122 --> 01:44:35,683
Thank you, Mr. President.

923
01:44:35,703 --> 01:44:36,083
Thank you.

924
01:44:36,103 --> 01:44:43,248
Good evening, Chief.

925
01:44:44,249 --> 01:44:45,330
Name and address of the record, please.

926
01:44:46,071 --> 01:44:50,534
Leo A. Sacco, Jr., 227 Elm Street, Medford, Chief of Police.

927
01:44:52,236 --> 01:44:54,137
I'm sorry, I don't mean to belabor your meeting.

928
01:44:54,177 --> 01:44:59,320
I know you're almost ready to move on to the next topic, but a few things were mentioned tonight that I have to clear up.

929
01:44:59,941 --> 01:45:04,283
I'm concerned about the people who are at home watching this and thinking that Medford is not a safe city.

930
01:45:05,884 --> 01:45:09,006
First and foremost, Medford is a very safe city.

931
01:45:09,426 --> 01:45:11,047
It's a very welcoming community.

932
01:45:11,888 --> 01:45:18,052
All you have to do is look at the real estate transfers and see what the prices are for the homes that are being sold in the city.

933
01:45:18,532 --> 01:45:20,713
People want to move to this community.

934
01:45:20,773 --> 01:45:21,894
People want to live here.

935
01:45:22,540 --> 01:45:25,601
people like this community because it is a safe community.

936
01:45:26,602 --> 01:45:35,105
I don't have the statistics with me this evening, but I can tell you this, that our crime rate in this, in this city is much lower than our surrounding communities.

937
01:45:35,806 --> 01:45:38,167
And that's one of the reasons why people want to live here.

938
01:45:38,767 --> 01:45:44,369
The low crime rate is directly related to the hard work of the men and women of the Medford police department.

939
01:45:45,029 --> 01:45:46,370
But beyond that,

940
01:45:47,628 --> 01:46:01,427
It's due to the work of the residents that live in the city, all residents that live in the city that are willing to call and report a crime, report a suspicious activity, report that they've been involved in, they've been the victim of a crime.

941
01:46:01,957 --> 01:46:06,321
And that's one of the things we're concerned about as a police department, that we don't want to stifle that.

942
01:46:06,781 --> 01:46:18,992
We want everyone to feel comfortable to come forward to the police, to report being a victim of a crime, to report what they may have seen in other criminal actions, which will help us to keep the city safe.

943
01:46:19,912 --> 01:46:26,836
Now it was said earlier by some members that were before this rail that the police department is being told what to do.

944
01:46:27,797 --> 01:46:29,678
Police department is not being told what to do.

945
01:46:30,138 --> 01:46:34,841
Police department is following the same practice and procedure that we've followed for many years.

946
01:46:35,642 --> 01:46:39,424
I've been a police officer 36 years in the city, 27 of them as chief.

947
01:46:40,064 --> 01:46:41,125
Nothing has changed.

948
01:46:42,065 --> 01:46:46,367
We do the same thing today that we did pretty much 36 years ago.

949
01:46:46,987 --> 01:46:51,069
So my entire career, we've been following the same practice and procedure.

950
01:46:51,509 --> 01:46:57,832
I can tell you that I very rarely asked anyone if they were a citizen of the United States.

951
01:46:58,552 --> 01:47:03,614
But if I put the handcuffs on someone and arrested them, there's a procedure that we follow.

952
01:47:04,455 --> 01:47:05,575
They come to the station.

953
01:47:06,216 --> 01:47:06,956
They are booked.

954
01:47:07,956 --> 01:47:09,737
In the booking, we get all their information.

955
01:47:10,738 --> 01:47:11,658
They are fingerprinted.

956
01:47:11,977 --> 01:47:13,999
The fingerprints go to the FBI.

957
01:47:15,200 --> 01:47:16,921
FBI shares them with other entities.

958
01:47:16,941 --> 01:47:20,644
So it goes to the state, then it goes to the FBI and they share it with the other entities.

959
01:47:21,605 --> 01:47:27,229
And sometimes it can be 10 minutes, sometimes it can be two hours, sometimes it can be as much as a day.

960
01:47:27,890 --> 01:47:35,096
We'll get something back saying that that person is not who they say they are because all arrests are backed up by fingerprints.

961
01:47:36,693 --> 01:47:41,657
And that's the only time we really know when someone may be in this country illegally.

962
01:47:41,717 --> 01:47:44,179
They may have been deported before and sent back.

963
01:47:44,879 --> 01:47:46,341
And there isn't anyone in this room.

964
01:47:46,421 --> 01:47:54,387
There isn't anyone in the city, anyone in the state or anyone in the country that doesn't want to see violent criminals arrested and dealt with regardless of their status.

965
01:47:55,268 --> 01:48:00,492
And I can assure you that they're not running loose because the Medford police are being sloppy or they're ignoring something.

966
01:48:01,052 --> 01:48:04,615
If they're, if they're out there, there's maybe some other glitch in the works.

967
01:48:05,077 --> 01:48:06,678
but it isn't the part of the police department.

968
01:48:06,718 --> 01:48:08,400
We make the arrests that need to be made.

969
01:48:09,380 --> 01:48:25,353
Sometimes I can tell you that it hasn't happened, at least in this past year, but I can tell you since probably November when the elections happened and January when that administration took office, the fear factor rose.

970
01:48:28,235 --> 01:48:31,698
It's probably because of all of the rhetoric about immigration enforcement.

971
01:48:32,469 --> 01:48:36,672
But nothing changed over the past several years or from the past several years.

972
01:48:37,072 --> 01:48:39,734
Everything we do is the same as what we did before.

973
01:48:40,975 --> 01:48:47,679
And we check everyone that we arrest and they go to Somerville District Court.

974
01:48:47,819 --> 01:48:53,863
If ICE calls us and said, we have a detainer for the person that you have, we don't hold them based on that detainer.

975
01:48:53,903 --> 01:48:56,125
We already had them under arrest for another charge.

976
01:48:57,119 --> 01:49:04,524
If they make bail or they end up being transported to Somerville District Court in the morning, ICE is told where those people will be.

977
01:49:04,905 --> 01:49:06,005
And that's the extent of it.

978
01:49:06,085 --> 01:49:07,666
We do not serve as ICE agents.

979
01:49:09,348 --> 01:49:13,370
Civil immigration laws are primarily the responsibility of the federal government.

980
01:49:13,811 --> 01:49:21,556
It's been said we're not, we don't have the resources to go knock on doors and check statuses, nor do we really have the interest to do that.

981
01:49:21,956 --> 01:49:24,118
We just, what will we do if we found them?

982
01:49:24,653 --> 01:49:26,374
Would ICE be able to respond and help us?

983
01:49:26,415 --> 01:49:27,175
They probably would not.

984
01:49:28,496 --> 01:49:41,207
By the same token, we're not being deputized to work as ICE agents, but if they call us because they're in the middle of something, if it's an officer safety issue, yes, we'll go help them to make sure that they don't get hurt or that no one else gets hurt.

985
01:49:42,668 --> 01:49:48,714
But I can tell you, we have not had a situation in the city of Medford that resulted at least in an ICE detainer that I know of.

986
01:49:49,234 --> 01:49:52,397
We have made several arrests, major league drug dealers,

987
01:49:53,652 --> 01:50:06,397
And we've sought information for mice and in a couple of cases that were detained as issued, but those are serious criminal criminals, criminal element that's bringing poison into our community and they had to be dealt with.

988
01:50:06,457 --> 01:50:18,261
And I don't think anyone disagrees with that being done, but I don't want anyone in the public, anyone that's watching this or anyone in this room tonight to think that the Medford police are going easy on crime or easy on the immigration issue.

989
01:50:19,142 --> 01:50:22,343
We work within the realm that we're dealt dealt with and uh,

990
01:50:23,885 --> 01:50:25,706
We do the best that we can with what we have.

991
01:50:26,646 --> 01:50:33,488
No one is going to escape what needs to be done, but we're not going out there looking just for the civil violation.

992
01:50:33,528 --> 01:50:35,208
That's not our focus.

993
01:50:35,648 --> 01:50:39,809
I think everyone agrees that we have far more important things that we need to do.

994
01:50:39,869 --> 01:50:43,410
But getting back to the main issue, Medford is a safe city.

995
01:50:43,470 --> 01:50:47,211
Whatever you want to call it otherwise, this is a safe city.

996
01:50:47,291 --> 01:50:48,832
People come here and we have

997
01:50:49,775 --> 01:50:51,838
Great police officers out there doing a great job.

998
01:50:51,879 --> 01:50:53,762
We definitely need more.

999
01:50:55,063 --> 01:50:57,924
but we're only as good as the information we receive from the public.

1000
01:50:57,964 --> 01:51:02,464
So we want all segments of the, of the public, uh, documented, undocumented.

1001
01:51:02,484 --> 01:51:07,885
We want people coming forward to, uh, if they're a witness of a crime to come forward and tell us what they saw.

1002
01:51:08,205 --> 01:51:21,088
We don't want anyone to be quiet and we don't want a segment of the community to be victimized because they're in fear of coming forward that they'd be exposed that no doubt be a victim of robberies on a regular basis.

1003
01:51:21,188 --> 01:51:21,288
So,

1004
01:51:22,322 --> 01:51:23,162
Thank you for your time.

1005
01:51:23,202 --> 01:51:24,382
I just wanted to clear that up.

1006
01:51:24,422 --> 01:51:26,383
If you have any questions, I'd be glad to answer them.

1007
01:51:26,403 --> 01:51:27,623
Thank you, Chief, for keeping us safe.

1008
01:51:28,283 --> 01:51:36,825
Name and address of the record, please.

1009
01:51:37,305 --> 01:51:40,705
Joe Villione, 59 Garfield Ave., Medford, Massachusetts.

1010
01:51:41,325 --> 01:51:43,466
